# Scratchpad

## Current task
Request log rotation 50MB + 3-month retention — COMPLETE

## Plan
- [X] Size-rotate dated files under `<sqlite_dir>/request_logs/`
- [X] Purge files older than 90 days
- [X] Config + status API + tests + UI copy

## Design
- Dir: `<data>/request_logs/requests-YYYY-MM-DD.log`
- Rotate to `requests-YYYY-MM-DD.N.log` at 50MB (`REQUEST_LOG_MAX_BYTES`)
- Retention 90 days (`REQUEST_LOG_RETENTION_DAYS`) by filename date
- Memory ring still 20k for Live Feed /admin/logs
- Toggle unchanged: PUT `/admin/request-logging`

## Lessons
- EventSource onerror fires on reconnect — never permanently close; reset on onopen + Reconnect button
- Live feed lagged because EventBus only published after SQLite flush — publish on enqueue + request add
- `max(100, max_entries)` blocked tests — floor at 1; production still uses max(100, settings)
- Persist toggles in sqlite `meta` via get_meta/set_meta
- Request log max_file_bytes floor must stay low (1) so unit tests can force rotation
